education related to the use of computers in organizations.wthe acm curriculum committee on computer educationfor management has been carrying out a study on "curriculum development in management informationsystems education in colleges and universities" under a grant from the national science foundation. this position paper provides a framework for the study.  preliminary conclusions are presented on theneed for education in administrative information systems, and appropriate college curricula and coursesare suggested.  also, the role of professional societies and organizations using computers is discussed,and the plans of the committee are outlined.  the initial approach of the committee has been to describethe education necessary for the effective use of computers in organizations, to classify thepositions for which education is required, and to survey educational programs now available.cacm september, teichroew, d..keducation, information analysis, systems design, business data processing.c. .ca jb february ,   : pm